1 (b) A mediator who receives a referral or an order from a
2 court to conduct mediation shall screen for the occurrence of
3 domestic abuse between the parties. A mediator shall not engage
4 in mediation when it appears to the mediator, or when either
5 party asserts, that domestic abuse has occurred, unless:
6 (1) Mediation is authorized by the alleged victim of the
7 domestic abuse; and
8 (2) Mediation is provided, in a specialized manner that
9 protects the safety of the alleged victim, by a
10 mediator who is trained in the field of domestic
11 abuse.
12 (c) An attorney or other individual designated by a party
13 may accompany the party to, and participate in, a mediation. A
14 waiver of participation given before the mediation may be
15 rescinded.
16 (d) As used in this section, "domestic abuse” has the same
